						<summary>

						<p>The Śaka year is doubtful as also the cyclic year. The latest known date of this chief is Śaka 1215 (No. 207 of 1936). The inscription records a gift of money received by way of fines by impoundage of cattle grazing on cornfields, as well as fees on rush plant collected from channel at Guṇḍalūr, for burning a lamp in the temple during the morning service of god Tiruvagattīśvaram-uḍaiyār. </p>						

						</summary>
